message: Are Wikipedia administrators going to do something about this? It is outrageous Binksternet continues to be selective. Now that he's lost the argument, he claims he's "done with the hoax". Yet, he was so willing to argue the Canadian Press article on Storch written by Evelyn McDonnell was a copy of the CBS article, which is not possible. This is an outrageous allowance of behaviour that is not conducive to editing wikipedia.q

The CBS article was written/published after Mrs. McDonnell's. Will anyone reel in Binksternet?
